Let's proceed step by step as requested.

### 1. List all atomic modeling claims made by the reference system model

#### Imports and Packages
1. The model imports `ScalarValues::Real`.
2. The model imports `TradeStudies::*`.
3. The model imports `Definitions::*`.
4. The model imports `Usages::*`.

#### Definitions Package
5. Defines part `Vehicle`.
6. Defines part `Engine`.
7. `Engine` has attribute `power` of type `ISQ::PowerValue`.
8. `Engine` has attribute `mass` of type `ISQ::MassValue`.
9. `Engine` has attribute `efficiency` of type `Real`.
10. `Engine` has attribute `reliability` of type `Real`.
11. `Engine` has attribute `cost` of type `Real`.
12. Defines part `Piston`.
13. Defines part `Cylinder`.
14. Defines part `ConnectingRod`.
15. Defines part `CrankShaft`.
16. Defines part `'4CylCrankShaft'` as a subtype of `CrankShaft`.
17. Defines part `'6CylCrankShaft'` as a subtype of `CrankShaft`.

#### Usages Package
18. Defines part `engine` of type `Engine`.
19. `engine` contains part `cyl[*]` of type `Cylinder`.
20. Each `cyl` contains part `p[1]` of type `Piston`.
21. Each `cyl` contains part `rod[1]` of type `ConnectingRod`.
22. `engine` contains part `cs` of type `CrankShaft`.
23. Defines a variation part `engineChoice` as a variation of `engine`.
24. `engineChoice` has variant part `'4cylEngine'`.
25. `'4cylEngine'` has 4 cylinders (`cyl[4]`).
26. `'4cylEngine'` uses `'4CylCrankShaft'` as `cs`.
27. `engineChoice` has variant part `'6cylEngine'`.
28. `'6cylEngine'` has 6 cylinders (`cyl[6]`).
29. `'6cylEngine'` uses `'6CylCrankShaft'` as `cs`.
30. Defines part `vehicle` of type `Vehicle`.
31. `vehicle` contains part `engine[1]` as a reference to `engineChoice`, defaulting to `'6cylEngine'`.
32. `vehicle.engine` has an assertion constraint `engineSelectionRational` referencing `Analysis::engineTradeStudy.selectedAlternative`.

#### Analysis Package
33. Defines calculation `EngineEvaluation`.
34. `EngineEvaluation` has input `power` of type `ISQ::PowerValue`.
35. `EngineEvaluation` has input `mass` of type `ISQ::MassValue`.
36. `EngineEvaluation` has input `efficiency` of type `Real`.
37. `EngineEvaluation` has input `cost` of type `Real`.
38. `EngineEvaluation` returns `evaluation` of type `Real`.
39. Defines analysis `engineTradeStudy` of type `TradeStudy`.
40. `engineTradeStudy` has subject `Engine[1..*]` set to all `engineChoice`.
41. `engineTradeStudy` has objective `MaximizeObjective`.
42. `engineTradeStudy` has calculation `evaluationFunction`.
43. `evaluationFunction` has input part `anEngine` as an alternative `Engine`.
44. `evaluationFunction` has calculation `powerRollup` (input: `engine = anEngine`, returns `power:>ISQ::power`).
45. `evaluationFunction` has calculation `massRollup` (input: `engine = anEngine`, returns `mass:>ISQ::mass`).
46. `evaluationFunction` has calculation `efficiencyRollup` (input: `engine = anEngine`, returns `efficiency: Real`).
47. `evaluationFunction` has calculation `costRollup` (input: `engine = anEngine`, returns `cost: Real`).
48. `evaluationFunction` returns `result : Real` as `EngineEvaluation(...)`.
49. `engineTradeStudy` returns part `selectedAlternative : Engine`.

---

**Total atomic claims:** 49
